  "title": "Assistant Sales Manager (Chemicals/Semiconductor)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:<br /></p><ul><li><p>Manage, grow, and retain existing customer accounts</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Drive business development with existing customers (new accounts, products, and market share growth)</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong relationships with key customer stakeholders</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal teams to resolve customer issues effectively</p></li><li><p>Prepare timely sales forecasts, business plans, proposals, and quotations</p></li><li><p>Monitor account status, ensure timely settlements, and flag potential credit risks</p></li><li><p>Develop deep understanding of customer needs, competitor activities, and market dynamics</p></li><li><p>Formulate and execute sales strategies to retain accounts and expand into new markets</p></li><li><p>Continuously update market intelligence on trends, technology, customers, and competitors</p></li><li><p>Provide pricing and commercial inputs to optimise profitability and margins</p></li><li><p>Track and evaluate account performance (monthly, quarterly, annually)</p></li></ul><p><br />Requirements:</p><ul><li><p>Degree in Chemistry, Chemical Engineering, Business</p></li><li><p>At least 4 years of sales experience in Chemical / Semiconductor Sector</p></li><li><p>Good knowledge of SAP & Salesforce</p></li></ul><p>Account Manager:<br />Kerwin Tan Kai Bin (R1331624)<br /><a href=\"mailto:kerwin.tan@searchasia.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">kerwin.tan@searchasia.com.sg</a><br />EA16S8107</p><p><br />\n\n</p>",
